properties.GAR_Description: The waters bounded by the polygon coordinates defined in WSSMUPU-02 excluding the intersection with the Antarctic coastline and the internal SSMUs. The subarea is divided between a pelagic area and the land-based predator area, with the latter area divided into four main units: Drake Passage, Elephant Island, Bransfield Strait and the Western Antarctic Peninsula. The Drake Passage and Bransfield Strait units are proposed to be divided into east and west components to delineate different foraging grounds of land-based predators.
